n Völker bis zum Ende des 6. Jahrhunderts. Abschließend werden die Schicksale der Provinzialen und deren Nachleben im Alpen- und nördlichen Voralpenraum behandelt. Ein Ausblick weist auf die hier deutlich werdenden Ursachen des Untergangs des (west-)römischen Reiches hin.  aThis book focuses on the decisive upheavals of the years after 375 A.D. in the Pannonian provinces, which were located between eastern Alps, the middle Danube, and the Adriatic Sea. It covers the Roman administration, the conquest by the Gothic Divisions, the development of the Visigoths and Ostrogoths as well as the appearance and eclipse of several peoples up to the late sixth century A.D. The treatment points out causal aspects that heralded the fall of the (western) Roman Empire.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAltertum. 0aAltertumskunde, germanische. 0aMigrations of nations. 0aMittelalter. 0aMitteldonaugebiet. 0aOstalpen. 0aVölkerwanderung. 4aAltertum. 4aAltertumskunde, germanische. 4aMittelalter. 4aMitteldonaugebiet. 4aOstalpen. 4aVölkerwanderung. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aBratoz, Rajko.1 aCastritius, Helmut.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI0 cprintz978311017855540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311089866840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110898668423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110898668/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014